narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: There are very few public econ courses offered so I was glad this one existed! Sun is a kind professor, and it was clear she was invested in our learning over the course of the semester. However, the course was pretty disorganized. The first few weeks when we covered models were great, but after that the course often diverged from the syllabus. We didn't end up covering the last 3 subjects on the syllabus, and missed 2 class sessions that were never rescheduled.
This course has extremely interesting theories!

Strengths: kind prof, interesting material, cool independent research project
Weaknesses: slightly disorganized

Strength: the Professor was incredibly engaging and took time to help students get familiar with the material, reading was manageable.

Weakness: because it was such a large seminar, I had less interaction with peers

Strengths: Some of the papers we read were really cool.

Weaknesses: Professor Lee. I heard great things about her from previous classes, but she was really disorganized this semester.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, conditional on a future iteration of the course being more organized and kept to seminar size. I'm glad I've had a semester of uban economics, but learned much less in this course than my other courses this semester.
